g4!! was played.}) 33... Ra8 (33... Rd5 $5 34. f4 Rc8 35. Be5 Kc5 36. g6 b4 ({
After} 36... Rxc6 $2 37. Rxc6+ Kxc6 38. Bf6 $1 Rd7 39. g7 $16 {it's Black who
has to look for escape.}) 37. g7 Kb5 38. Ra7 Rg8 39. c7 Kb6 40. Ra4 Rxe5 41.
fxe5 Kxc7 42. Rxb4 Rxg7 43. Rc4+ Kb6 44. Rd4 $15 {and White should be able to
keep a draw.}) 34. Bd6+ $1 ({Definitely not} 34. Rb6 $2 Kc5 $19) 34... Kc4 35.
Rb6 $1 (35. Rxa8 Rxa8 36. c7 Kd5 37. Be7 Kc6 38. Bd8 b4 $19 {and Black should
