42. Rd6+ Kf5 (42... Kg4 43. f3+ Kg3 44. Rg6+ Kh2 45. Rh6 Ra1+ 46. Kf2 Ra2+ 47.
Kf1 Ra1+ 48. Kf2 $11) 43. f3 e4 44. Rd5+ Ke6 45. fxe4 $11) 38... Kc4 39. Rd8 $4
$138 {This was already too much. On the last seconds of the first time control
I had noticed that I promote the g-pawn with a check, but as usually happens I
missed Black's very first move.} (39. Rc6+ $11) 39... Ra1+ $1 40. Ke2 Rxc7 $19
{Now despite a strong g-pawn White's position is lost.} 41. Bf6 Rg1 {This move
came as a complete surprise.} (41... Ra2+ $5) 42. g3 (42. Bxe5 {was a tougher
